  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ebola Response Lubero - CBCA Appeal</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to reduce the risk of Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) contamination in South Lubero, North Kivu - DRC through community engagement and improving hygienic practice .  Affected communities will be  mobilized to consult and collaborate with Ebola response teams and reduce resistance. Access to hygiene materials to promote  hygiene  lead to good and consistently applied Wash practices  help prevent human to human transmission of EVD. finally community will also be trained to produce a DDR plan for the EVD</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">By the end of the project implementation period, people living in the affected areas will benefit from project&apos;s outcomes to accept and collaborate with the reposte team and minimize the resistance. wash facilities infrastructures will be improved to offer  appropriate and fair hygienic environment to prevent form Ebola risk contamination. People in the communities will be enable with communication skills to develop a DDR action plan.</narrative>
  </description>
